# Step 1: Ensure you meet the requirements
* The 3 current requirements for running for President are:
 https://www.whitehouse.gov/about-the-white-house/our-government/the-executive-branch/ 3 current requirements
[x] The President must be at least 35 years of age
 - I am 39. I was born in 1984.
[x] The President must be be a natural born citizen
 - I was born in Brockton, Massachusetts.
[x] The President must have lived in the United States for at least 14 years.
 - I have lived in the United States my entire life.

# Step 2: Adhere to FEC requirements
 https://www.fec.gov/help-candidates-and-committees/registering-candidate/ FEC requirements
[] Designate a principal campaign committee
 [] Appoint a treasurer
 [] Appoint an assistant treasurer
 [] Appoint custodian of records
 [x] Complete Statement of Organization
  https://webforms.fec.gov/webforms/form1/index.htm
[] Raise $5,000 in contributions or spend $5,000 in expenditures
[x] Obtain an EIN
 https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/how-to-apply-for-an-ein EIN
[] Get a bank account
 - All bank accounts must be opened in the name of the committee using the committee’s Employer Identification Number. Bank accounts should never be opened in the name of an individual using an individual’s Social Security Number.
 https://www.fec.gov/help-candidates-and-committees/get-tax-id-and-bank-account/
[] Understand requirements for matching funds
 https://www.fec.gov/help-candidates-and-committees/understanding-public-funding-presidential-elections/establishing-eligibility-presidential-primary-matching-funds/
[] Gain ballot access in all 50 states
 https://www.fec.gov/help-candidates-and-committees/registering-candidate/gaining-ballot-access/
[] Complete Statement of Candidacy
 https://webforms.fec.gov/webforms/form2/index.htm

# Step 3: To Receive Matching Funds
[] Raise $5,000 in 20 states
 - You must have at least 20 donors in each state
 - An individual can contribute a maximum of $3,300
  https://www.fec.gov/updates/contribution-limits-for-2023-2024/#:~:text=The%20inflation%2Dadjusted%20limits%20are,per%20calendar%20year)%20(52%20U.S.C.
 - But only up to $250 per person counts toward the $5,000 figure

